In this lesson, I will show you how to build an Angular Material data datable that is sortable and filterable, while maintaining a realtime connection with Firestore. A dialog modal will be used share data between material components and update documents in Firestore.
This tutorial also makes suggestions for performance optimization when dealing with hundreds rows in the view. The end result is a table that&hellip;
Uses Firebase/Firestore as the data source.
